1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:01,600
<i> There he is!</i>

2
00:00:02,767 --> 00:00:05,633
<i>This whole time,
I was thinking about him,</i>

3
00:00:05,633 --> 00:00:08,233
<i>but he already had
someone else in mind.</i>

4
00:00:08,233 --> 00:00:10,367
I understand how you feel, Jade.

5
00:00:10,367 --> 00:00:13,767
<i>I have chosen
to love you silently.</i>

6
00:00:13,767 --> 00:00:16,700
<i>Because you are more
important than my feelings.</i>

7
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,767
<i>What? And just like that,
he's free again?</i>

8
00:00:18,767 --> 00:00:21,600
<i> Because of that,
</i>we've just been in more danger.

9
00:00:21,600 --> 00:00:23,200
<i> You betrayed me.</i>

10
00:00:23,200 --> 00:00:25,200
<i> You ruined our lives, Dad.</i>

11
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,200
<i>Your selfishness
has consumed you.</i>

12
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,367
[MAP RIPS]

13
00:00:28,367 --> 00:00:30,367
- [PUNCHES]
- [GROANING]

14
00:00:30,367 --> 00:00:32,200
<i> I've got another copy!</i>

15
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:34,000
<i>And Michael's kids
have the others.</i>

16
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:35,533
<i>Once we put
all the pieces together,</i>

17
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,567
nothing will be able to stop us.

18
00:00:39,133 --> 00:00:40,500
[BOTONG] Close your eyes.

19
00:00:41,233 --> 00:00:43,367
And feel the wind.

20
00:00:43,367 --> 00:00:45,633
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

21
00:00:45,633 --> 00:00:48,200
The shadows will listen.

22
00:00:49,767 --> 00:00:52,100
The trails of the one
who has vanished...

23
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:54,767
will be revealed.

24
00:00:58,067 --> 00:01:00,400
He found out when Monette died.

25
00:01:01,267 --> 00:01:03,767
Do you think he'd also
find out who killed her?

26
00:01:03,767 --> 00:01:07,367
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

27
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:09,167
My grandfather has never failed.

28
00:01:09,167 --> 00:01:10,133
[BOTONG SHUSHES]

29
00:01:10,567 --> 00:01:12,133
[TRIXIE] I'm sorry.

30
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:13,433
Grandpa...

31
00:01:14,100 --> 00:01:16,067
Can you see something yet?

32
00:01:18,767 --> 00:01:20,100
[SARI] Grandpa?

33
00:01:21,267 --> 00:01:22,667
[BOTONG] He's not far off.

34
00:01:22,667 --> 00:01:24,467
[MYSTERIOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

35
00:01:24,467 --> 00:01:27,133
Monette's killer is just
around the corner.

36
00:01:29,467 --> 00:01:31,033
[BOTONG] Be careful.

37
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,367
He has no intention of stopping.

38
00:01:40,300 --> 00:01:41,700
[SANDRO GRUNTING]

39
00:01:41,733 --> 00:01:48,667
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

40
00:01:49,633 --> 00:01:51,600
[SANDRO] Drink. Here.

41
00:01:52,467 --> 00:01:53,767
Drink.

42
00:01:54,567 --> 00:01:55,800
[WATER SPLASHES]

43
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:58,767
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

44
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:07,367
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:02:07,367 --> 00:02:11,500
You asked me why the treasure
was so important to me.

46
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:16,133
It was because of my son.

47
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,767
It was for Juan.

48
00:02:20,167 --> 00:02:21,767
That was our mission.

49
00:02:22,867 --> 00:02:26,400
We badly wanted to get it
ever since he was a kid.

50
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:29,233
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

51
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:30,600
[SANDRO] But he's already gone.

52
00:02:32,567 --> 00:02:35,467
But that doesn't mean
that I'm going to stop.

53
00:02:36,467 --> 00:02:42,433
My desire to get what I want
has only grown stronger.

54
00:02:44,833 --> 00:02:47,400
So that's why you wanted
to kill Dad and the others.

55
00:02:48,467 --> 00:02:50,700
All because of your mission.

56
00:02:53,800 --> 00:03:00,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:56,000
[LUNA] Gio and I decided
that none of us

58
00:03:56,000 --> 00:03:58,300
should come to Hotel 88 for now.

59
00:03:58,900 --> 00:04:00,233
But why?

60
00:04:00,500 --> 00:04:01,867
For everyone's safety.

61
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:06,300
We also need to focus
on finding Leon.

62
00:04:06,967 --> 00:04:08,300
I agree.

63
00:04:09,533 --> 00:04:12,900
We don't know
what might happen next.

64
00:04:13,933 --> 00:04:15,700
[JADE] But what about
Gio and his brothers?

65
00:04:15,700 --> 00:04:17,967
If you're telling us that
it's dangerous in the hotel,

66
00:04:17,967 --> 00:04:20,533
then shouldn't they also
get out of there?

67
00:04:22,467 --> 00:04:23,833
They didn't want to leave.

68
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:26,433
If I were them,
I wouldn't leave too.

69
00:04:27,367 --> 00:04:29,367
I'd rather die than back down.

70
00:04:29,367 --> 00:04:30,600
[FRIDA] Justin!

71
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:31,733
I'm just saying.

72
00:04:33,433 --> 00:04:38,267
[CELLPHONE RINGING]

73
00:04:38,267 --> 00:04:39,400
Excuse me.

74
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,433
Hello?

75
00:04:41,433 --> 00:04:42,633
[KIKO] Jade?

76
00:04:42,633 --> 00:04:44,700
<i> We have to meet tomorrow.</i>

77
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:45,733
<i> Will that be fine?</i>

78
00:04:45,733 --> 00:04:46,900
Okay, sure.

79
00:04:46,900 --> 00:04:51,467
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

80
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:52,600
[PHONE DINGS]

81
00:04:58,367 --> 00:05:00,400
[TRIXIE] Justin.
We need to meet tomorrow.

82
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,000
<i> We'll send you the details.</i>

83
00:05:02,033 --> 00:05:04,333
<i> Please don't tell anyone.</i>

84
00:05:08,333 --> 00:05:09,433
What's that?

85
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:11,000
[LUNA] Who texted you?

86
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:14,000
Nothing.

87
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:16,333
It was just a friend who
was checking on me.

88
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:20,633
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

89
00:05:20,633 --> 00:05:24,433
[SANDRO] Mike and Federico
deserve to die

90
00:05:24,433 --> 00:05:26,533
for everything they did to me.

91
00:05:28,667 --> 00:05:30,467
They didn't stop going after me.

92
00:05:31,533 --> 00:05:33,900
After they ran over me...

93
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,300
they pushed me off the cliff.

94
00:05:42,833 --> 00:05:44,400
Are you saying that...

95
00:05:44,867 --> 00:05:47,300
you're the one who killed them?

96
00:05:47,833 --> 00:05:54,800
[GRIM MUSIC PLAYING]

97
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,067
[BREATHING SHARPLY]

98
00:05:57,067 --> 00:05:58,400
You're an animal!

99
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,467
- You should've died already!
- [CHAINS CLANKING]

100
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:01,967
You bastard!

101
00:06:02,833 --> 00:06:03,967
[LEON] You're an animal!

102
00:06:05,367 --> 00:06:06,967
What did you think of me?

103
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:09,433
A weakling?

104
00:06:09,867 --> 00:06:14,833
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

105
00:06:14,833 --> 00:06:16,433
[SANDRO] As the saying goes,

106
00:06:16,433 --> 00:06:18,400
a person with a mission

107
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:21,100
does not go down easily.

108
00:06:24,033 --> 00:06:27,833
- [SANDRO GRUNTING]
- [SQUELCHING]

109
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:36,833
[GRIM MUSIC CONTINUES]

110
00:06:36,833 --> 00:06:39,433
[GRUNTING CONTINUES]

111
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:41,833
[PANTING]

112
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:44,467
[SANDRO GRUNTING]

113
00:06:44,467 --> 00:06:46,433
[SANDRO] Your fathers buried me.

114
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:49,567
They didn't know
that I was still alive.

115
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:52,367
I rose up from my grave.

116
00:06:53,867 --> 00:06:57,833
[SANDRO GROANING]

117
00:06:57,833 --> 00:07:01,800
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

118
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:03,767
[SANDRO] My body was in tatters.

119
00:07:04,000 --> 00:07:05,567
I forced myself to stand up.

120
00:07:06,833 --> 00:07:09,800
[GROANING]

121
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:12,600
[COUGHING]

122
00:07:12,600 --> 00:07:14,400
[SANDRO] I had to live...

123
00:07:14,933 --> 00:07:16,633
for my son.

124
00:07:17,533 --> 00:07:19,100
For the treasure.

125
00:07:19,100 --> 00:07:23,467
[GROANING IN PAIN]

126
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:26,033
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

127
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:28,033
[LEON] And you really
chose to live here.

128
00:07:29,667 --> 00:07:31,033
Where should I be instead?

129
00:07:32,633 --> 00:07:33,867
Here...

130
00:07:34,967 --> 00:07:38,833
I can watch your every move.

131
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,833
- [INHALES SHARPLY]
- [CHAINS CLANKING]

132
00:07:40,833 --> 00:07:43,833
[SANDRO] While I was
waiting for you to learn

133
00:07:43,833 --> 00:07:45,600
about the treasure...

134
00:07:46,167 --> 00:07:48,433
I was just here, below you.

135
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:50,833
Rotting away.

136
00:07:51,167 --> 00:07:53,133
[SANDRO] Until one day...

137
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:56,200
Michael's children came here.

138
00:07:56,200 --> 00:07:57,600
That!

139
00:07:57,867 --> 00:08:02,067
That was the signal
that they finally found

140
00:08:02,067 --> 00:08:04,500
the treasure I was looking for.

141
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:08,500
[MICHAEL]<i> How can I ever
</i> trust you, you bastard?!

142
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,933
[FEDERICO] I don't know
what you're talking about!

143
00:08:09,933 --> 00:08:10,933
[MICHAEL] What do you mean?

144
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:12,933
<i> I help my end of the bargain!</i>

145
00:08:12,933 --> 00:08:14,767
That when we found the treasure,

146
00:08:14,767 --> 00:08:17,033
<i> we would split it equally!</i>

147
00:08:17,033 --> 00:08:19,700
<i>But you partnered up
with that bastard Sandro</i>

148
00:08:19,700 --> 00:08:21,033
<i> who set the hotel on fire!</i>

149
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:23,533
<i>If Sandro had really
set the hotel on fire,</i>

150
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:24,967
<i> I had nothing to do with it!</i>

151
00:08:24,967 --> 00:08:26,633
<i> But you know that man!</i>

152
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:27,900
Isn't he your business partner?!

153
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:31,667
<i> He just wanted me to be
</i>a partner in his casino project!

154
00:08:31,867 --> 00:08:33,800
<i> But I didn't accept his offer!</i>

155
00:08:34,267 --> 00:08:35,667
<i> Wait a minute!</i>

156
00:08:35,667 --> 00:08:37,800
<i>You might have forgotten
that between the two of us,</i>

157
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:40,267
<i>I wasn't the one who
betrayed our friendship.</i>

158
00:08:40,267 --> 00:08:42,033
<i> - It was you!
- Me?</i>

159
00:08:42,033 --> 00:08:45,033
<i> You and Frida betrayed me!</i>

160
00:08:45,967 --> 00:08:48,167
<i>How many times
do I have to tell you?</i>

161
00:08:48,167 --> 00:08:50,233
<i>Your wife and I
don't have a relationship!</i>

162
00:08:51,933 --> 00:08:54,067
<i>Even though I know
you're both deceiving me...</i>

163
00:08:55,267 --> 00:08:57,700
<i>I still held up my end
of our deal.</i>

164
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,767
<i>Our deal that when
we find the treasure...</i>

165
00:09:02,567 --> 00:09:04,067
<i> we will tell each other.</i>

166
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:08,767
<i> I told you that when
</i>I found the treasure, didn't I?

167
00:09:09,767 --> 00:09:12,033
<i> Mike, believe me.</i>

168
00:09:12,533 --> 00:09:14,200
I'm not in cahoots with Sandro.

169
00:09:14,867 --> 00:09:16,767
[FEDERICO]<i> We even
</i> took care of him, didn't we?

170
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,667
[Federico]<i> If I was really
</i> an accomplice to his plan,

171
00:09:20,667 --> 00:09:22,800
<i>then I should've killed you
a long time ago!</i>

172
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:27,967
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

173
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,800
<i> And why do you have a gun?</i>

174
00:09:30,333 --> 00:09:32,300
[FEDERICO]
<i> Are you that angry with me?</i>

175
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:34,567
<i> You were ready to kill me?!</i>

176
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:44,867
[MICHAEL] I'm sorry about that.

177
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:47,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

178
00:09:47,867 --> 00:09:50,067
<i>I just got carried away
by my emotions.</i>

179
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,867
<i> But, you know that</i>

180
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,833
<i> no matter how angry I am...</i>

181
00:09:57,967 --> 00:10:00,200
<i> I can't kill you.</i>

182
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:09,200
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

183
00:10:09,200 --> 00:10:14,633
[GASPING]

184
00:10:14,633 --> 00:10:15,767
<i> How?</i>

185
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:17,333
<i> - No.
</i>- [GUN CLANKS]

186
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,567
[SANDRO] Don't.

187
00:10:23,300 --> 00:10:24,867
[GUN CLANKS]

188
00:10:24,867 --> 00:10:31,833
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

189
00:10:37,300 --> 00:10:38,867
[GUN CLICKS]

190
00:10:39,067 --> 00:10:40,200
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GROANS]

191
00:10:41,067 --> 00:10:42,633
- [GUNSHOT]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

192
00:10:46,900 --> 00:10:49,733
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

193
00:10:49,733 --> 00:10:50,867
[GUNSHOT]

194
00:10:51,733 --> 00:10:55,133
[SCRAPING]

195
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:56,267
- [GRUNTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

196
00:11:00,033 --> 00:11:01,900
[GUN CLANKING]

197
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:02,867
[GUNSHOT]

198
00:11:04,300 --> 00:11:06,267
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

199
00:11:06,267 --> 00:11:13,233
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

200
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:16,967
[SANDRO] I killed them!

201
00:11:18,133 --> 00:11:20,100
And you...

202
00:11:20,667 --> 00:11:23,300
You were left here at the hotel.

203
00:11:23,900 --> 00:11:26,800
You did nothing but argue!

204
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,867
All day, every day!

205
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:31,933
[SANDRO] Even in simple stuff...

206
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:33,967
you still fought!

207
00:11:35,033 --> 00:11:38,333
But I'm grateful for
your non-stop fights.

208
00:11:39,133 --> 00:11:42,267
Because while you were
arguing with each other...

209
00:11:42,833 --> 00:11:45,467
you never thought that...

210
00:11:45,467 --> 00:11:48,767
I was looking for someone
who could tell me

211
00:11:48,767 --> 00:11:53,333
where your fathers
hid away my treasure!

212
00:11:55,133 --> 00:11:57,100
But you didn't find anything.

213
00:11:57,100 --> 00:12:00,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

214
00:12:00,100 --> 00:12:02,200
Do you think...

215
00:12:03,033 --> 00:12:04,867
that you'd still be alive today

216
00:12:04,867 --> 00:12:06,833
if I already found
the treasure?!

217
00:12:07,367 --> 00:12:08,400
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

218
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:09,967
[SANDRO] You.

219
00:12:10,433 --> 00:12:14,800
I'm going to use you
to get what I want!

220
00:12:14,833 --> 00:12:16,933
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

221
00:12:16,933 --> 00:12:18,767
You're a bastard, Sandro!

222
00:12:23,833 --> 00:12:26,433
[CHUCKLING]

223
00:12:31,833 --> 00:12:33,267
- [KIKO] Jade.
- Kiko.

224
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:36,433
Luna said we shouldn't go
to the hotel anymore.

225
00:12:36,867 --> 00:12:38,433
It's too dangerous.

226
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,400
But this is an exception.

227
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,667
Jade, I need your help.

228
00:12:43,267 --> 00:12:44,133
Why? What's the matter?

229
00:12:44,133 --> 00:12:46,467
We need to go back
to that church.

230
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:47,633
In Oscalara.

231
00:12:48,533 --> 00:12:50,300
They killed Monette.

232
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:52,933
That means they're
getting closer to us.

233
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:58,967
The treasure is the only thing
that can protect us right now.

234
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,233
Okay.

235
00:13:06,233 --> 00:13:12,533
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

236
00:13:15,633 --> 00:13:16,967
[SANDRO] For the treasure...

237
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,300
I can be an animal.

238
00:13:23,333 --> 00:13:25,400
The first guest at the hotel.

239
00:13:27,333 --> 00:13:30,300
They came only a few weeks
after the death of your fathers.

240
00:13:32,300 --> 00:13:33,600
He suddenly disappeared.

241
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,767
He didn't disappear.

242
00:13:37,433 --> 00:13:38,567
I killed him.

243
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:42,433
[LEON] Why?

244
00:13:42,633 --> 00:13:45,533
[SANDRO] Because he wanted
to steal my treasure.

245
00:13:46,467 --> 00:13:47,633
[SANDRO GRUNTING]

246
00:13:47,633 --> 00:13:48,933
- [RUSTLING]
- [GRUNTS]

247
00:13:55,533 --> 00:13:56,533
Bok.

248
00:13:56,867 --> 00:13:58,433
He was also our guest.

249
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:01,400
The police also
found him dead.

250
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,933
Ah, Bok.

251
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:07,733
[SANDRO] You should
thank me for that.

252
00:14:07,733 --> 00:14:11,000
Because he wanted to kill
Gio, Martin, and Kiko.

253
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,700
I just protected them.

254
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,533
Why would you protect them

255
00:14:17,533 --> 00:14:19,333
when they're also
trying to find the treasure?

256
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:25,833
Because Mike and Fred
left all the maps to you.

257
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:31,500
And you can't die
until you discover that.

258
00:14:31,533 --> 00:14:33,000
So if they die...

259
00:14:33,700 --> 00:14:36,667
my efforts would go to waste.

260
00:14:42,800 --> 00:14:43,933
[SANDRO EXHALES]

261
00:14:43,933 --> 00:14:44,900
[CREAKS]

262
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:51,867
[DARK MUSIC PLAYING]

263
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,067
That belongs
to Peter Montevilla.

264
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,567
[BAG THUDS]

265
00:15:03,133 --> 00:15:04,600
Did you kill him too?

266
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:10,633
[SANDRO] He saw the tunnel
that I use to go here.

267
00:15:12,533 --> 00:15:13,667
[BODY THUDS]

268
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:16,000
[SANDRO] And he saw me.

269
00:15:16,700 --> 00:15:17,900
You're a monster!

270
00:15:19,067 --> 00:15:20,433
[SANDRO] Mm.

271
00:15:20,433 --> 00:15:21,933
So why should I hold back?

272
00:15:21,933 --> 00:15:22,967
After all...

273
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,400
I've already confessed to you.

274
00:15:25,833 --> 00:15:27,500
[SANDRO] Your friend Vito...

275
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:28,600
- [CHAINS RATTLING]
- [HUFFS]

276
00:15:30,133 --> 00:15:32,033
You should have
left him out of this.

277
00:15:33,567 --> 00:15:35,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

278
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:37,500
It was your fault.

279
00:15:39,667 --> 00:15:41,567
You got him involved.

280
00:15:42,700 --> 00:15:44,500
[SANDRO] He saw me.

281
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,800
- [VITO SCREAMING IN PAIN]
- [STABS]

282
00:15:46,700 --> 00:15:47,833
[YELLING]

283
00:15:47,833 --> 00:15:49,833
- [STABS]
- [GROANS IN PAIN]

284
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:53,533
I'd get caught
if I didn't kill him.

285
00:15:56,633 --> 00:15:58,167
And then there was Monette.

286
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,700
[CHAINS RATTLING]

287
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:01,067
You bastard!

288
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:02,500
[SANDRO] Monette...

289
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,867
That was the time I saw

290
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:08,933
how you and your six siblings
fell apart.

291
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:10,967
[SANDRO] I feel bad for her.

292
00:16:12,033 --> 00:16:13,567
Poor girl.

293
00:16:14,967 --> 00:16:17,967
You keep saying that
all seven of us are siblings.

294
00:16:17,967 --> 00:16:20,533
Uncle Mike's children
are not my brothers.

295
00:16:21,767 --> 00:16:23,633
Because in my eyes...

296
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,900
you're all brothers and sisters.

297
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:32,867
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

298
00:16:33,767 --> 00:16:34,967
Where are you going?

299
00:16:37,867 --> 00:16:40,567
[SANDRO] Who was the last person
my son talked to

300
00:16:40,567 --> 00:16:41,867
before he died?

301
00:16:44,933 --> 00:16:46,067
Justin...

302
00:16:47,867 --> 00:16:49,533
Don't hurt him.

303
00:16:50,067 --> 00:16:52,067
Don't hurt my brother!

304
00:16:52,833 --> 00:16:54,933
No. No!

305
00:16:55,867 --> 00:16:57,167
No!

306
00:16:57,167 --> 00:16:58,467
Sandro, no!

307
00:16:58,767 --> 00:16:59,967
Come back here!

308
00:17:00,867 --> 00:17:02,033
Sandro!

309
00:17:02,967 --> 00:17:04,433
[LEON] No!

310
00:17:04,800 --> 00:17:05,833
No!

311
00:17:06,767 --> 00:17:08,800
[CHAINS RATTLING, CLANKING]

312
00:17:08,800 --> 00:17:11,633
[LEON] No! Sandro, don't do it!

313
00:17:11,633 --> 00:17:12,900
- [CHAINS RATTLING, CLANKING]
- Come back here!

314
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:14,933
Sandro!

315
00:17:17,767 --> 00:17:18,833
No!

316
00:17:19,733 --> 00:17:21,133
- No!
- [CHAINS RATTLING]

317
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:24,167
No!

318
00:17:25,700 --> 00:17:26,900
[GRUNTING]

319
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:33,100
[STIRRING MUSIC PLAYING]

320
00:17:33,100 --> 00:17:37,000
One map was engraved in stone,
the other on a tombstone.

321
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,533
The one we're looking for
must be hidden here somewhere.

322
00:17:39,533 --> 00:17:46,500
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

323
00:17:51,067 --> 00:17:52,833
Jade.

324
00:17:52,833 --> 00:17:53,967
I'll lift it
so you can take a look.

325
00:17:53,967 --> 00:17:54,967
Okay.

326
00:17:57,967 --> 00:18:00,900
[CERAMIC SCRAPING]

327
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:05,233
- Is it there?
- No, Kiko.

328
00:18:07,033 --> 00:18:09,100
I don't know where else to look.

329
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,967
[SIGHS] Oscalara.

330
00:18:12,267 --> 00:18:14,300
That's our only clue.

331
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:20,967
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

332
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:22,367
What could that be?

333
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:26,467
Maybe this isn't the
Oscalara mentioned in the book.

334
00:18:27,267 --> 00:18:28,567
Maybe it's a person.

335
00:18:28,567 --> 00:18:33,233
Or maybe Oscalara
is somewhere else.

336
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:36,467
Oscalara?

337
00:18:36,467 --> 00:18:38,100
Are you looking for Oscalara?

338
00:18:38,100 --> 00:18:40,467
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

339
00:18:40,467 --> 00:18:44,167
Is there another place
called Oscalara?

340
00:18:44,433 --> 00:18:46,100
Yes, there is.

341
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:49,033
There was a place here
on the island called Oscalara.

342
00:18:49,033 --> 00:18:50,067
Really?

343
00:18:51,233 --> 00:18:52,467
Before the Arellanos

344
00:18:52,467 --> 00:18:54,900
bought the land
in San Marcelino,

345
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:57,133
it used to be called Oscalara.

346
00:18:57,167 --> 00:18:59,533
They renamed it San Marcelino.

347
00:19:00,233 --> 00:19:01,333
Jade.

348
00:19:03,167 --> 00:19:05,267
That's where you teach the kids.

349
00:19:07,133 --> 00:19:10,600
All this time...
Oscalara was right there.

350
00:19:11,933 --> 00:19:13,467
Why are you looking for it?

351
00:19:13,467 --> 00:19:17,933
[STIRRING MUSIC CONTINUES]

352
00:19:17,933 --> 00:19:20,000
[LEAVES RUSTLING]

353
00:19:24,933 --> 00:19:26,333
Here.

354
00:19:26,333 --> 00:19:28,500
Mark that, Trixie.

355
00:19:29,233 --> 00:19:32,233
Monette could've run by here.

356
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:36,567
- Careful, you might get hurt.
- Okay.

357
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:37,733
What are you doing?

358
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:41,267
[SIGHS SHARPLY] Finally.
It's about time you got here.

359
00:19:41,267 --> 00:19:43,167
What the hell are you doing?

360
00:19:43,167 --> 00:19:45,900
We're marking the trees
Monette could've passed by.

361
00:19:46,300 --> 00:19:47,500
Maybe we'll find a--

362
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:49,433
[JUSTIN]
Why are you so stubborn?

363
00:19:49,433 --> 00:19:51,600
Didn't your brothers
tell you to go home?

364
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,567
Wait.

365
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:54,433
Calm down, Justin.

366
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:57,167
Hear us out first.

367
00:19:58,367 --> 00:20:01,000
Grandpa Botong
performed a ritual.

368
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:02,633
He said...

369
00:20:02,667 --> 00:20:04,600
the killer's nearby.

370
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,367
He's still here.

371
00:20:07,467 --> 00:20:09,667
- And you believed him?
- [CHESKA HUFFS]

372
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:14,167
Justin,
he knows Monette is dead.

373
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:17,200
Aren't you scared
for your lives?

374
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:19,667
- Grandpa Botong said--
- Please!

375
00:20:19,667 --> 00:20:22,567
Trixie, Cheska, listen to me.

376
00:20:23,033 --> 00:20:24,367
Go home.

377
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:27,200
We already have
enough on our plates.

378
00:20:27,200 --> 00:20:28,267
Excuse me?

379
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:32,367
Are you saying
we're being a burden?

380
00:20:32,367 --> 00:20:33,567
That's not what I said.

381
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:35,233
But that's what you meant,
isn't it?

382
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:36,667
[MOUTH CLICKS] No.

383
00:20:37,467 --> 00:20:38,533
No.

384
00:20:39,200 --> 00:20:41,100
Don't gaslight me, Cheska.

385
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:43,600
I'm only concerned
about your safety.

386
00:20:44,767 --> 00:20:47,033
[SIGHS] Justin...

387
00:20:47,033 --> 00:20:48,700
- Come here.
- Geez.

388
00:20:50,433 --> 00:20:53,067
Miss Jade, we haven't had
arts and crafts in a while.

389
00:20:53,067 --> 00:20:55,533
I'm sorry, I've been busy.

390
00:20:55,533 --> 00:20:56,767
How are you doing here?

391
00:20:56,767 --> 00:20:58,700
Same as always. We're okay.

392
00:20:59,433 --> 00:21:01,500
Sir Edward's not with you?

393
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:03,267
Ah...

394
00:21:03,467 --> 00:21:06,600
No, he must be busy.

395
00:21:06,600 --> 00:21:08,167
O-Okay. Excuse me.

396
00:21:08,200 --> 00:21:09,700
I need to talk to someone.

397
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:11,233
- Okay.
- Okay.

398
00:21:14,233 --> 00:21:16,067
I have a question.

399
00:21:16,067 --> 00:21:20,400
Is it true that this area
used to be called Oscalara?

400
00:21:21,133 --> 00:21:23,133
Yes, but that was
a long time ago.

401
00:21:23,133 --> 00:21:24,767
A very long time ago.

402
00:21:25,333 --> 00:21:26,667
Wait.

403
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:28,467
Why are you asking about it?

404
00:21:29,033 --> 00:21:31,767
How did you find out
about Oscalara?

405
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,333
Show her, Jade.

406
00:21:36,467 --> 00:21:37,733
Because of this.

407
00:21:40,033 --> 00:21:41,567
"Five of them were standing,

408
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,633
but not walking.

409
00:21:44,233 --> 00:21:46,433
Follow the path that--"

410
00:21:47,267 --> 00:21:48,433
What's the matter?

411
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:51,200
I'm not the one
you should be asking.

412
00:21:52,400 --> 00:21:54,333
What do you mean?

413
00:21:54,333 --> 00:21:57,267
Why? What do you know
about these words?

414
00:21:58,067 --> 00:22:00,200
There's Tamara.

415
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,533
She's the one you should ask.

416
00:22:01,533 --> 00:22:04,300
Her grandmother
knows everything.

417
00:22:05,300 --> 00:22:07,367
- Thank you.
- Ma'am, is she...

418
00:22:07,767 --> 00:22:09,067
[WOMAN BREATHES SHAKILY]

419
00:22:09,067 --> 00:22:13,700
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

420
00:22:15,433 --> 00:22:16,500
Good morning.

421
00:22:17,133 --> 00:22:18,533
Are you Tamara?

422
00:22:20,333 --> 00:22:21,567
What do you want?

423
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,233
That lady brought us here.

424
00:22:25,233 --> 00:22:27,533
She said your grandmother
might be able to help us.

425
00:22:30,533 --> 00:22:31,667
With what?

426
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:38,600
Do you know what this means?

427
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:45,600
[INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING]

428
00:22:46,433 --> 00:22:48,000
Go away.

429
00:22:48,400 --> 00:22:51,567
Our family has suffered enough
because of those words.

430
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:54,133
Wait.
We only have one question.

431
00:22:54,133 --> 00:22:56,167
No. Goodbye.

432
00:22:56,167 --> 00:22:58,233
T-Tamara, please.

433
00:22:58,233 --> 00:23:01,067
Please, you're the only one
who can help us.

434
00:23:01,067 --> 00:23:02,000
[GATE CLOSES]

435
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,467
We are deeply indebted
to the Arellanos.

436
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:08,100
If you're not one of them,
you won't get anything from us.

437
00:23:12,167 --> 00:23:13,567
Did you hear that?

438
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:16,200
They'll only help an Arellano.

439
00:23:17,733 --> 00:23:19,400
Wait, maybe I can convince them.

440
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:20,600
Jade, I don't think so.

441
00:23:21,100 --> 00:23:22,333
Let's go home.

442
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:24,667
We have to respect
their wishes.

443
00:23:28,367 --> 00:23:29,767
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]

444
00:23:33,067 --> 00:23:34,500
What is it?

445
00:23:35,433 --> 00:23:37,067
Justin texted me.

446
00:23:40,500 --> 00:23:41,500
Come on.

447
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:45,500
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

448
00:23:45,500 --> 00:23:46,633
[JUSTIN] This way.

449
00:23:47,633 --> 00:23:49,400
I told Kiko you didn't go home.

450
00:23:49,400 --> 00:23:51,333
- What? Justin!
- Why?

451
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:53,300
If you don't want
your brothers to get mad,

452
00:23:53,300 --> 00:23:55,333
we'll go back to the hotel.

453
00:23:55,367 --> 00:23:56,633
Alright? Let's go.

454
00:23:57,467 --> 00:23:58,700
[RUSTLING]

455
00:24:01,433 --> 00:24:03,367
Don't even think about it.

456
00:24:03,367 --> 00:24:04,367
Justin.

457
00:24:04,367 --> 00:24:06,333
What part of the map
do you think this is?

458
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:08,500
Where are we right now
on the map?

459
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,500
[JUSTIN] Cheska, enough.

460
00:24:10,500 --> 00:24:12,067
Please.

461
00:24:13,833 --> 00:24:15,367
I never should've given you

462
00:24:15,367 --> 00:24:17,567
the map I found
at Sandro's house.

463
00:24:19,300 --> 00:24:21,833
You two are out of control.

464
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:23,467
[CHESKA] Justin,
I don't have the map anymore.

465
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:25,700
I gave it to Kiko. Ask Trixie.

466
00:24:25,700 --> 00:24:26,767
[TRIXIE]
Kiko has the map,

467
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:28,533
and the brothers
will look at it.

468
00:24:28,567 --> 00:24:31,133
Map or no map,
there's no stopping you two.

469
00:24:32,133 --> 00:24:34,633
[TRIXIE] Justin,
we just wanted to help.

470
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:41,367
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

471
00:24:41,367 --> 00:24:44,567
Kiko... Kiko...

472
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:47,333
You have my map.

473
00:24:48,833 --> 00:24:50,733
<i> The hotel
has ceased operations.</i>

474
00:24:50,733 --> 00:24:53,233
<i>The closure is for
the safety of all of us.</i>

475
00:24:53,233 --> 00:24:54,300
<i> You are not leaving, Jade.</i>

476
00:24:54,300 --> 00:24:55,467
<i> She can't leave, Ma.</i>

477
00:24:55,467 --> 00:24:58,567
<i>Everyone who leaves this house
doesn't come back.</i>

478
00:24:58,567 --> 00:25:00,700
- [KEYBOARD CLACKS]
<i> - Your enemy is wise.</i>

479
00:25:02,300 --> 00:25:03,800
[GRUNTING HARD]

480
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,333
[SCREAMING IN PAIN]

481
00:25:05,333 --> 00:25:07,300
<i> What's wrong, Cheska?</i>

482
00:25:07,300 --> 00:25:08,433
<i> You're planning something.</i>

483
00:25:08,433 --> 00:25:10,400
<i> I will look for the treasure.</i>

484
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:11,600
<i> Are you serious?</i>

485
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,467
<i>That Sandro is a threat
to our lives</i>

486
00:25:13,467 --> 00:25:15,500
<i>because he
wants to get all the clues.</i>

487
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:16,867
[THUDS]

488
00:25:16,867 --> 00:25:18,333
[BODY THUDS]

489
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:20,767
<i> Who are you?</i>

490
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:21,667
<i> Help!</i>

491
00:25:21,667 --> 00:25:24,300
<i> - Someone is chasing me!
</i>- [YELLING]

492
00:25:24,300 --> 00:25:25,633
<i>- Kiko, say something!
- Kiko!</i>

493
00:25:25,633 --> 00:25:26,867
<i> Hurry! Come on!</i>

494
00:25:26,867 --> 00:25:28,900
- [GRUNTS]
- [BODY THUDS]

495
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,300
<i> Where's my map?!</i>

496
00:25:31,300 --> 00:25:32,800
<i>- You're an idiot, Martin!
- [CLANKS]</i>

497
00:25:32,800 --> 00:25:34,133
- Do you want to get hurt? Here!
- [BLOW LANDS]
